snippet.textDisplay: I think the reason Oppenheimer did a lot better than Thanos is because it's a lot easier to make jokes about Thanos, and as a result, a lot easier to insult him. Boasting about yourself doesn't have as much impact as insulting your opponent. How many roasts was Thanos really able to make outside of very general chemistry jokes? A few, but almost all of Oppenheimer's lines are referencing something clever, which is why ironically as the lesser known character he probably has the edge.
snippet.textOriginal: I think the reason Oppenheimer did a lot better than Thanos is because it's a lot easier to make jokes about Thanos, and as a result, a lot easier to insult him. Boasting about yourself doesn't have as much impact as insulting your opponent. How many roasts was Thanos really able to make outside of very general chemistry jokes? A few, but almost all of Oppenheimer's lines are referencing something clever, which is why ironically as the lesser known character he probably has the edge.
